1 AMEND House Substitute for House Committee Substitute for House Bill Nos. 3068 & 3049,
2 Page 42, Section 304.822, Line 138, by inserting after all of said section and line the following:
3
4 "307.179. 1. As used in this section, the following terms shall mean:
5 (1) "Child booster seat", a seating system which meets the Federal Motor Vehicle Safety
6 Standards set forth in 49 C.F.R. 571.213, as amended, that is designed to elevate a child to
7 properly sit in a federally approved safety belt system;
8 (2) "Child passenger restraint system", a seating system which meets the Federal Motor
9 Vehicle Safety Standards set forth in 49 C.F.R. 571.213, as amended, and which is either
10 permanently affixed to a motor vehicle or is affixed to such vehicle by a safety belt or a universal
11 attachment system;
12 (3) "Driver", a person who is in actual physical control of a motor vehicle.
13 2. Every driver transporting a child under the age of sixteen years shall be responsible,
14 when transporting such child in a motor vehicle operated by that driver on the streets or
15 highways of this state, for providing for the protection of such child as follows:
16 (1) Children under three years of age shall be secured in a rear-facing child passenger
17 restraint system; except that such child may be secured in a forward-facing child passenger
18 restraint system when the child reaches the highest rear-facing weight or height allowed by the
19 manufacturer of the particular rear-facing system;
20 (2) Except as provided under subdivision (1) of this subsection, children [less than]
21 under four years of age, regardless of weight, shall be secured in a child passenger restraint
22 system appropriate for that child;
23 [(2)] (3) Except as provided under subdivision (1) of this subsection, children weighing
24 less than forty pounds[, regardless of age,] and under eight years of age shall be secured in a
25 child passenger restraint system appropriate for that child;
26 [(3)] (4) Children at least four years of age but [less than] under eight years of age, who
27 also weigh [at least] forty pounds [but less than eighty pounds, and who are also less than four
28 feet, nine inches tall,] or more, shall be secured in a child passenger restraint system or booster
29 seat appropriate for that child;
