1 [(4)] (5) Children at least eighty pounds [or children] and more than four feet, nine
2 inches in height, or at least eight years of age, shall be secured by a vehicle safety belt [or
3 booster seat appropriate for that child] in accordance with section 307.178;
4 [(5)] (6) A child who otherwise would be required to be secured in a booster seat may be
5 transported in the back seat of a motor vehicle while wearing only a lap belt if the back seat of
6 the motor vehicle is not equipped with a combination lap and shoulder belt for booster seat
7 installation[;
8 (6) When transporting children in the immediate family when there are more children
9 than there are seating positions in the enclosed area of a motor vehicle, the children who are not
10 able to be restrained by a child safety restraint device appropriate for the child shall sit in the
11 area behind the front seat of the motor vehicle unless the motor vehicle is designed only for a
12 front seat area. The driver transporting children referred to in this subsection is not in violation
13 of this section.
14
15 This subsection shall only apply to the use of a child passenger restraint system or vehicle safety
16 belt for children less than sixteen years of age being transported in a motor vehicle].
17 3. Any driver who violates subdivision (1), (2), [or] (3), or (4) of subsection 2 of this
18 section is guilty of an infraction and, upon conviction, may be punished by a fine of not more
19 than fifty dollars and court costs. Any driver who violates subdivision [(4)] (5) of subsection 2
20 of this section shall be subject to the penalty in subsection 6 of section 307.178. If a driver
21 receives a citation for violating subdivision (1), (2), [or] (3), or (4) of subsection 2 of this
22 section, the charges shall be dismissed or withdrawn if the driver prior to or at his or her hearing
23 provides evidence of acquisition of a child passenger restraint system or child booster seat which
24 is satisfactory to the court or the party responsible for prosecuting the driver's citation.
25 4. The provisions of this section shall not apply to any public carrier for hire. The
26 provisions of this section shall not apply to students four years of age or older who are
27 passengers on a school bus designed for carrying eleven passengers or more and which is
28 manufactured or equipped pursuant to Missouri Minimum Standards for School Buses as school
29 buses are defined in section 301.010.
30 5. The highways and transportation commission shall initiate and develop a program of
31 public information to develop understanding of, and ensure compliance with, the provisions of
32 this section."; and
33
34 Further amend said bill by amending the title, enacting clause, and intersectional references
35 accordingly.
